<br>
I've never really pinpointed exactly what it is that I dislike.  People have asked me this repeatedly and I have no solid answer.  The graphics are good, the scenery is great, the concepts are organized, mythic is a great company that listened to its beta testers, the playability is easy.<br>
<br>
There's just something that makes me just scream inside.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Now I know that Shadowbane will be the next game I put time into and we're waiting for hubby to get into the beta, he just updated his beta info so we're looking forward to seeing how that game goes.  I guess I just like EQ, even with all its quirkiness and problems.  I started playing online games with Meridian59 and the community was so close, and when a server matures on EQ it is nice, like that community feeling.  Ah well, morning rambling done <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
