<br>
She's never been disenchanted with the 'end game' (Gah, I hate that term... I want a living world, not Doom: Final Level!), she has kept her distance from most of the politics *cough* and she has never had a problem looking for groups.  I, on the other hand, get wrapped up in the politics too much, had to accept that EverQuest forced an end game and forced your role in that end game, and I also hate the who LFG thing.<br>
<br>
I think part of it too is that even in Beta, I had friends playing and didn't have to feel alone, while most of her friends were still in EverQuest.  Now, many of her friends have moved to Dark Age, but I think she's kind of happy with the break there as well.<br>
<br>
Overall, I have never kidded myself that everyone is going to love Dark Age.  They have implemented some of the things we grumbled for in Dark Age Beta (like the friends list, yay!) and actually it's nicer than EQ had.  It tells you when a friend logs in and leaves and also has a little screen you can turn on to see your friends that are online.<br>
<br>
I think my attitude was that I loved the EverQuest community, but was completely fed up with the game and the lack of interest I saw in changing the problems in the game.  Those that don't like Dark Age tend to not be impacted by all of those game-related problems of EQ.  The one comment people make about a weakness in Dark Age is a sense of community.  UO people said the same thing about EQ in its first six months.  But we made our community there, and we are making it in Dark Age as well.<br>
<br>
So don't feel alone.  I think you would see a different issue when it comes to the community already, but then again maybe you wouldn't.  It's not going to be a game for everyone, but then no game will be.  Some people swore they would never leave UO for EQ, and some of them never did.  That's the beauty and bane of the human spirit - we aren't all the same.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
